external_knowledge:
- "Gardeners" refers to customers;
- "Seeds they have sown" refers to the number of vaccinations;
- "The most recent seed they planted" refers to the latest vaccination;
- "Active gardeners" refers to customers whose status is "Yes".

- "Active in the community" refers to the `active` column indicating if a customer is currently active (Yes/No);
- "Guardian angel in times of need" refers to the `emergency_contact_name` and `emergency_contact_phone` columns;
- "Journey through vaccinations" refers to the `vaccination_status` column and the count of completed vaccinations;
- "Sought the wise counsel of healers" refers to the `consultation_count` from the `ConsultationDetails` CTE;
- "Number of diagnoses" refers to the `diagnosis_count` from the `ConsultationDetails` CTE.

- "brave souls" refers to customers who have completed their COVID-19 vaccination;
- "navigated the labyrinth of multiple consultations" refers to having more than one consultation;
- "infectious disease specialist" refers to a doctor with the specialization 'Infectious Diseases';
- "after the dawn of 2022" refers to consultations that occurred after January 1, 2022.

- "vaccination centers" are facilities where people can receive vaccinations;
- "customer vaccinations" refer to the instances where customers have been vaccinated;
- "consultations" are the medical consultations that precede or are associated with the vaccinations.

- "Top vaccination status entry" refers to the vaccination status with the highest number of vaccinations for each customer.;
- "Prioritizing" in this context means selecting the entry with the highest count of vaccinations for each customer.;
- "History" refers to the complete record of vaccinations and consultations for each customer.

- "fully vaccinated" means the customer has received all required doses of the vaccine;
- "still blooming" refers to customers who are active;
- "completed their vaccine journey" indicates that the vaccination status in the `customer_vaccinations` table is 'Completed'.

- "seeds" metaphorically refers to the reports created by users;
- "garden of knowledge" metaphorically refers to the system or database where reports are stored;
- "each gardener" metaphorically refers to each user in the system.
